              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant chronic medical conditions. She was born at term via normal vaginal delivery and has met all developmental milestones. She is fully vaccinated according to the Czech immunisation schedule. She has had approximately two to three episodes of upper respiratory tract infection per year since starting kindergarten [MEDLINEPLUS:J00], all self-limiting. She had a tonsillectomy at age 4 due to recurrent tonsillitis. She has no history of hospitalisation for respiratory illness and no known asthma or allergic airway disease. Her mother reports a mild allergy to amoxicillin (urticarial rash noted at age 3). There are no smokers in the household. Her diet is balanced and she is active."
          }
        ]
      }
